  "text": "The Kafka consumer fetch request to record processing chain consists of the following stages:\n\n**1. Request Building Stage:**\nWhen a consumer calls poll(), it invokes Fetcher.sendFetches() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/Fetcher.java:105). This method calls AbstractFetch.prepareFetchRequests() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/AbstractFetch.java:412) to determine which partitions need to be fetched and construct FetchRequest.PartitionData for each partition, including topic IDs, fetch offsets, fetch sizes, and leader epochs. The requests are grouped by target broker node.\n\n**2. Fetch Request Builder Stage:**\nFor each node with partitions to fetch, AbstractFetch.createFetchRequest() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/AbstractFetch.java:301) creates a FetchRequest.Builder. This builder is configured with:\n- API version (determined by topic ID support)\n- Max wait time and minimum bytes\n- Isolation level (read_committed or read_uncommitted)\n- Max bytes per fetch\n- Fetch session metadata (via FetchSessionHandler)\n- Rack ID for replica selection\n\n**3. Network Sending Stage:**\nFetcher.sendFetchesInternal() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/Fetcher.java:184) sends the FetchRequest.Builder instances via ConsumerNetworkClient.send() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerNetworkClient.java:107). The request is queued in the unsent requests queue and response futures with listeners are registered.\n\n**4. Network Polling Stage:**\nThe actual network IO occurs when ConsumerNetworkClient.poll() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/ConsumerNetworkClient.java:243) is called, which delegates to the underlying KafkaClient to send requests over the network and receive FetchResponse objects from brokers.\n\n**5. Response Processing Stage:**\nWhen a FetchResponse is received, AbstractFetch.handleFetchSuccess() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/AbstractFetch.java:150) is invoked. This method:\n- Parses the FetchResponse using FetchSessionHandler to get the per-partition data\n- Creates CompletedFetch objects for each partition from FetchResponseData.PartitionData\n- Stores these CompletedFetch objects in the FetchBuffer\n\n**6. Record Collection Stage:**\nFetchCollector.collectFetch() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/FetchCollector.java:92) processes CompletedFetch objects from the FetchBuffer. For each CompletedFetch:\n- It checks if the partition is assigned and fetchable\n- Calls CompletedFetch.fetchRecords() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/CompletedFetch.java:252) to extract up to maxPollRecords ConsumerRecord objects\n\n**7. Record Deserialization Stage:**\nCompletedFetch.fetchRecords() iterates through RecordBatch objects and calls CompletedFetch.parseRecord() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/CompletedFetch.java:307) for each record. This method:\n- Extracts the key and value ByteBuffers from the record\n- Deserializes the key using the configured key deserializer\n- Deserializes the value using the configured value deserializer\n- Creates a ConsumerRecord object with the topic, partition, offset, timestamp, headers, and deserialized key/value\n\n**8. Final Assembly Stage:**\nThe ConsumerRecord objects are accumulated in a Fetch object (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/Fetch.java) which groups records by TopicPartition. Finally, in ClassicKafkaConsumer or AsyncKafkaConsumer, a ConsumerRecords object (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/ConsumerRecords.java) is created from the Fetch's records map and returned to the application.\n\nKey supporting components:\n- FetchSessionHandler (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/FetchSessionHandler.java) manages fetch sessions and tracks session state across requests\n- FetchRequestManager (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/internals/FetchRequestManager.java) in the newer async consumer provides an alternative implementation for the fetch request creation and polling\n- FetchBuffer manages buffered CompletedFetch objects for efficient memory usage\n- FetchMetricsManager tracks metrics like fetch latency and partition lag throughout the process"
}

